  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Most of buidler's instability comes from using web3, and in particular web3-provider-engine.\r\n\r\nWe should consider using [ethers.js](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/) instead. We could create an ethers-powered web3 shim if necessary.\r\n\r\nI haven't had enough time to experiment on this yet, but I think it's a promising idea. Still, it would be a big change, so I'll like to get some feedback about it.",
